The paper deals with computer vision algorithms and their performance in virtual worlds, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of computer graphics to generate virtual worlds suggests that it may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The paper also discusses tracking, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of deep learning algorithms suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of weather and imaging conditions on recognition performance, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
